title: For Sale:  Finn Finland or Finnish Mosin M24
postcontent:
Hi, what we have here is a desireable and highly sought after Finnish made M24, manufactured using a German made Bohler Stahl barrel.

The rifle exudes history from stock to finish, the only visible detractor from it is that it has a mismatched serialized bolt, which is fairly common place among Mosins.

This one is not counterbored and has the correct stock finish and original bluing, plenty of rifling left and a nice tight muzzle with what looks to be the original crown. 

There are a few (dime size?) A and W stamps (a couple of which actually look raised) on this stock that I believe indicate Austrian use, it also has a small wooden dowel type plug on the bottom where an Austrian style swivel would/might have been screwed in at one time.

Either way the Russian M91 butt part of the stock was later reused and fingerspliced by the "Finn's" into what it is now.

I would like $400.00 for this one in a face to face sale in the Richmond, Henrico, Mechanicsville area.


Sling and loops are not part of this sale.

I have not fired this one so I cannot attest to it's accuracy or function, it is exactly as I bought it years ago.

Don't miss out on the opportunity to own this nice piece with no shipping charges or auction hassles and anxiety. 

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Custom Winchester Mod 54 in 9.3 x 62 Mauser
postcontent: The Model 54 is the predessor of the Model 70 which came being in 1937. This controlled feed with Mauser style claw extractor Winchester action was made in 1936 one of the last ones ever made. The custom work includes, 25” Lothar Walther stainless steel match grade barrel which was bead blasted for a matte finish. NECG front and rear sights have been added and include three front inserts,one is white, one red fiber optic and lastly a brass one with two hoods. The custom stock is made from Turkish fiddle back walnut that was cut in 1968 and made into the stock in 2004, with a rosewood forend tip added. The stock is an old English style with a pancake cheek piece which has been glass bedded. Pachmyr Old English thin recoil pad added. The action, bottom metal, scope bases, extractor, grip cap, sling studs, screws, recoil lug cross bolts, bolt shroud and safety are grey parkerized to hold up to the elements well. The action is smooth and has a really nice trigger! Weight is approximately 8.5 lbs with a 14” LOP. The gun shoots great and has not been hunted with. There are a couple of dings in the stock from be handled and the safe. I have tried to capture them in the photos. Selling my Smith and Wesson 300 I got off in a trade.

This is a particularly rare shotgun. Smith and Wesson had very little to do with the shotgun market. This being produced in the 1980's during the scare of all American manufacturing being sent overseas to Japan... This shotgun is infact manufactured in Japan. Yep, good ol' S&W outsourcing to Japan.

This shotgun was competing against the Remington 870 for federal police contracts. However, the Remington 870 was made in the United States; a little bit of conspiracy theories here and there. The Remington 870 was given the contract. title: For Sale:  AK 74 Bulgarian matching parts 5.45 x 39
postcontent:
Brand new Bulgarian AK 74 (ammo in picture is sold separately).

High quality, all matching,  Bulgarian made surplus rifle parts sets and brand new U.S. parts including barrel and receiver combined with top grade professional assembly makes for a fantastic rifle. 

Each of the rifles begins as a grade 1 all stamped matching Bulgarian AK-74 parts set.
Parts are then professionally assembled by the importer onto a Nodak Spud AK-74 high cap receiver and fitted with a brand new ESS barrel. 

U.S. Parts include Barrel, Receiver, 3 piece G-2 No Slap Trigger set by Tapco, and U.S. made Pistol Grip.

Rifle also features the highly effective and original Bulgarian AK-74 compensator... These things are too cool.

Note - I love this comp and would never change it , but, if you wish to do so it is simply threaded on and can be removed easily
by depressing the retaining plunger pin and un-threading it. It can be replaced with any standard 14x1 left hand threaded compensator.

All metal parts on the rifles look new and are indeed either new or like new in condition.

Original wood furniture has been re-finished to like new condition.
See the picture of the forearm and gas tube cover.... Forearm is the really nice palm swell type and upper covers are beautiful.

Assembly is done to the highest of professional standards ... i.e. no hammers and anvils here.
All metal surfaces are smooth and clean, all rivets are machine seated and overall finish is to original factory standards. 

All rifles are test fired and re-cleaned before being boxed to ship. 

Each rifle includes 2 -30 round mag and is backed by a one year warrenty by the manufacturer. 

A word about barrels. AK-74's have gotten a bad wrap on some forums due to some manufacturers using barrels that were not bored properly which led to rifles being inaccurate or bullets that would keyhole downrange.... That is not the case here - These barrels are made by ESS, one of the premiere civilian and military contract barrel manufacturers in the U.S.  -  They are done right.

We have tested these rifle extensively and they have fired accurately with all bullet weights and brands. 

The rifle bores on these rifles are a true 5.45 diameter and we have been very impressed with the accuracy...

MS residents 7%, 3% cc's, $25 shipping.

The Model 98B rifle’s aluminum upper receiver boasts an 18-inch M1913 optics rail, offering plenty of space to mount substantial optics as well as a night vision device or other accessories. The forward receiver is drilled and tapped for accessory rails to be mounted at the 3, 6 and 9 o’clock positions. This impressive long-range weapon isn’t all work. Equipped with a rear monopod and forward bipod, it’s also a pleasure to shoot. location: South Minneapolis, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Brand New In Box, never mounted or fired

If you are looking for the most accurate and powerful round that can be used in an upper that fits an AR-15 lower, the 6mm AR Turbo 40° Improved round developed by Robert Whitley, an expert shooter and frequent contributor to AccurateShooter.com and Precision Shooting magazine, is probably as good as it gets.

The description of his highly acclaimed products such as match-grade uppers and custom reloading supplies, including detailed information on the 6mm AR Turbo 40° Improved highlighted here, can be found at his website: http://www.6mmar.com.

To achieve this level of performance, please note that this round is a custom cartridge that requires reloading. The case must first be resized using the 6.5 Grendel brass with a special custom sizing die and then "fire-formed" to achieve the 40° case shoulder. If you are not familiar with these reloading steps and techniques or do not want to perform these necessary steps to reload your own ammunition, this is NOT for you. Commercial ammunition is not currently available.

I purchased this complete 6mm AR Turbo 40 Improved upper along with all necessary parts for reloading from Robert Whitley through his company AR-X Enterprises. LLC on November 5, 2012.

This upper has a 26" Krieger match barrel with a thick-walled DPMS upper receiver and has the right-side charging handle. It comes complete with 2 bolts - the original and an upgraded Nickel Boron-plated high performance bolt. The front ventilated FF tube has a bipod stud as well as a movable handstop complete with a QD swivel. 3 spent cases are also included.

The reloading kit comprises the customized Redding seating and Competition micrometer seating dies, with the correct shellholder and a .266 Titanium Nitride bushing. Spare pin and allen key, 6AR T40 loading instructions are also included. To complete the upper are 4 15 round magazines and a cleaning guide rod.

Are items are brand new, never been mounted, used or fired (other than test firing for the spent cases before my purchase).
